Run ``ty server`` with its working directory set to the project root. ty's
environment discovery (which interpreter or ``.venv`` it resolves the standard
library against) previously depended on the directory ``strict-kwargs`` was
invoked from, so the same project could produce different results when checked
from different locations. Resolution is now reproducible regardless of the
caller's working directory; as a result the ``ty`` fallback also resolves some
project-relative function-local imports it previously missed, flagging those
keyword-able positional calls (issue #200).
